<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi></placeName>, (Received) <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-13"><hi rend="italic">March 13,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Thompson reports that the terms proposed by Da Gama have been declined by
                        the Government, and that the city is practically deserted. The insurgents
                        have not returned the fire of the loyal forts which commenced at noon. The
                        firing from the batteries in the city will begin at 3.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>